{"entryType":"UniProtKB reviewed (Swiss-Prot)","primaryAccession":"Q9UHB9","secondaryAccessions":["B3KUU5","B3KWY7","G3V1U4","Q8NCJ4","Q8WUK2"],"uniProtkbId":"SRP68_HUMAN","entryAudit":{"firstPublicDate":"2001-01-11","lastAnnotationUpdateDate":"2026-01-28","lastSequenceUpdateDate":"2003-09-26","entryVersion":200,"sequenceVersion":2},"annotationScore":5.0,"organism":{"scientificName":"Homo sapiens","commonName":"Human","taxonId":9606,"lineage":["Eukaryota","Metazoa","Chordata","Craniata","Vertebrata","Euteleostomi","Mammalia","Eutheria","Euarchontoglires","Primates","Haplorrhini","Catarrhini","Hominidae","Homo"]},"proteinExistence":"1: Evidence at protein level","proteinDescription":{"recommendedName":{"fullName":{"value":"Signal recognition particle subunit SRP68"},"shortNames":[{"value":"SRP68"}]},"alternativeNames":[{"fullName":{"value":"Signal recognition particle 68 kDa protein"}}]},"genes":[{"geneName":{"value":"SRP68"}}],"comments":[{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250","source":"UniProtKB","id":"P38687"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"16672232"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"27899666"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"34020957"}],"value":"Component of the signal recognition particle (SRP) complex, a ribonucleoprotein complex that mediates the cotranslational targeting of secretory and membrane proteins to the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) (PubMed:34020957). The SRP complex interacts with the signal sequence in nascent secretory and membrane proteins and directs them to the membrane of the ER (PubMed:34020957). The SRP complex targets the ribosome-nascent chain complex to the SRP receptor (SR), which is anchored in the ER, where SR compaction and GTPase rearrangement drive cotranslational protein translocation into the ER (PubMed:34020957). Binds the signal recognition particle RNA (7SL RNA), SRP72 binds to this complex subsequently (PubMed:16672232, PubMed:27899666). The SRP complex possibly participates in the elongation arrest function (By similarity)"}],"commentType":"FUNCTION"},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000250","source":"UniProtKB","id":"Q00004"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"16672232"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"27899666"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"28369529"}],"value":"Heterodimer with SRP72 (PubMed:16672232, PubMed:27899666, PubMed:28369529). SRP68/SRP72 heterodimer formation is stabilized by the presence of 7SL RNA (By similarity). Component of a signal recognition particle (SRP) complex that consists of a 7SL RNA molecule of 300 nucleotides and six protein subunits: SRP72, SRP68, SRP54, SRP19, SRP14 and SRP9 (By similarity). Within the SRP complex, interacts (via C-terminus) with SRP72 (via N-terminus) (PubMed:16672232, PubMed:27899666, PubMed:28369529)"}],"commentType":"SUBUNIT"},{"commentType":"INTERACTION","interactions":[{"interactantOne":{"uniProtKBAccession":"Q9UHB9","intActId":"EBI-1048560"},"interactantTwo":{"uniProtKBAccession":"P13569","geneName":"CFTR","intActId":"EBI-349854"},"numberOfExperiments":7,"organismDiffer":false},{"interactantOne":{"uniProtKBAccession":"Q9UHB9","intActId":"EBI-1048560"},"interactantTwo":{"uniProtKBAccession":"P09132","geneName":"SRP19","intActId":"EBI-2680090"},"numberOfExperiments":6,"organismDiffer":false},{"interactantOne":{"uniProtKBAccession":"Q9UHB9","intActId":"EBI-1048560"},"interactantTwo":{"uniProtKBAccession":"O76094","geneName":"SRP72","intActId":"EBI-1058850"},"numberOfExperiments":9,"organismDiffer":false},{"interactantOne":{"uniProtKBAccession":"Q9UHB9-2","intActId":"EBI-12210563"},"interactantTwo":{"uniProtKBAccession":"Q9UHD9","geneName":"UBQLN2","intActId":"EBI-947187"},"numberOfExperiments":3,"organismDiffer":false}]},{"commentType":"SUBCELLULAR LOCATION","subcellularLocations":[{"location":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"10618370"}],"value":"